task.summary: Default task
Replaced old app with new app, which does not use MVVM much anymore
Added most automatable parameters for motion effect, and added general automation slot (double/float for now) that can be used for anything

Improved rendering performance by applying track opacity in the final frame assembly, instead of applying it to the track's surface itself. Also improved property editor, fixed key frame insertion and made the clip's automation editor support effect parameters too
Got the resource drag-drop working on clips, started working on improved action system
Added basic shortcut actions like slice, move track up/down/top/bottom, new video track
Added some basic context menus for clips, tracks and track control surfaces

Added timecode clip, added automatic resource loader that shows a GUI to fix invalid resource data which will be used when opening projects and enabling resources that were disabled by the user, also added context entries to tracks to insert clips, and fixed possible memory leaks/bugs where cached AdvancedMenuItem children were not cleared, and finally fixed bug where playback fps didn't match project settings
Exporting video now works, via File>Export
Added automatable vector2 parameter, improved render data disposal syncronisation in video track, fixed crashing when deleting tracks or clips due to no track/clip available in ASDC

Fixed desynchronisation of ResourceManager selected items. Added track drag-drop registry, renamed ResourceItem Enable function to be more descriptive of the intention; Enable is meant to be an "auto-enable" feature
Added new content to README
Fixed desynchronisation of timeline track selection collection

Added modal dialogs for messages/inputs, added more actions and shortcuts (rename track, clip, resource), fixed shortcut manager firing multiple shortcuts when a previous one was executed successfully, fixed advanced action menu item, removed unused imports, and fixed resource explorer's current folder not being synced with the resource manager
Added AVMedia clip and resource and improved resource documentation

New sexy rendering performance!!!! Added render stall evasion, which tries to skip frames if the render takes too long while not skipping too far (due to encoder seeking), massively improved rendering performance by letting clips tell the track the effective area that pixels were modified in so that tracks aren't copying their entire bitmap into the final bitmap, removed unnecessary pixel copy from RenderManager to SKAsyncViewPort, and finally added MediaFrameOffset (used by AVMediaVideoClip) which is hopefully self explanatory

Added project serialisation, added clip drag-copy feature to drag and drop a cloned clip by holding CTRL, fixed property editors not hiding when not applicable, added shortcut activation message in the activity bar, made timecode clip thread safe (I hope...), fixed duplicate input strokes in context menus, fixed possible bug where multiple resource entries use the same id of 0, added hardware decoder support for AVMediaVideoClip although I don't think it works most the time, added primary/secondary expander states and no-expander state to property editor groups, and finally made AutomationData update the backing storage after deserialising/cloning
Added project settings dialog that lets you edit resolution and frame rate

Added font size to timecode clip, fixed issues with automation updates not happening and key frames being inserted when they aren't supposed to be, added clip content controls (only used by image clips at the moment)
Added video track effect support (default project has motion effects for all tracks), started adding support for composition clips, added property editor slots for tracks,
Updated README with 2 more pictures and info
Added automation activity LED for property editor slots
